Boil a full #kettle{}. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Add the potato chunks
to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the
@cucumber{1/2}, then halve lengthways. Cut lengthways into roughly 1cm wide strips,
then cut into 1cm pieces widthways. Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%carton} in a
#sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add
the garlic and @North Indian style spice mix{1%sachet} and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, butter beans and
@water for the sauce{50%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in large #bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and @sugar for the
dressing{1/2%tsp}. Add the cucumber, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.
Add a knob of @butter for the sauce{20%grams} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash the
potatoes with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover
with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the @mango chutney{40%grams} and butter.
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel
it needs it. Remove from the heat.

Next, add the @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} to the bowl with the cucumber. Just
before you're ready to serve, toss the @baby leaf mix{50%grams} through the dressing.

Share the mash between your plates and top with the curried beans. Sprinkle the cheese
over the beans. Serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!